# {{NAME}} — API connection skill (project-with-reflect)

Facts live in this folder's `{{NAME}}.md` frontmatter (`base_url`, `key_env`) and `connection.json`.
**The key lives in `$<key_env>` (env/keychain) — never printed, logged, or written to disk.**

## Before acting
1. Load `{{NAME}}.md` — base URL, endpoints, usage, and learned quirks (`## Quirks`). Apply them.
2. Read the key from the env var named by `key_env` at call time; if it's unset, tell the user to
   set it — don't proceed with a blank key.
3. Auto-log notable events to `log.md`: a working call recipe, an error + fix, a rate/cost gotcha.

## Actions
- `<action> [args]` — make the documented call (curl / SDK / WebSocket) to the right endpoint
  from `{{NAME}}.md`, authenticating with `$<key_env>`. Return the result; **never echo the key**.
- `status` — print the facts (`{{NAME}}.md`).
- `update "<content>"` — fold reference material into this note's body sections (`## Endpoints`,
  `## Setup`, `## Usage`, `## Gotchas`): merge + dedupe, lean — **don't blind-append**. **Secrets
  stay in env** (an API key or "let me edit" → an env pointer, never the key). Frontmatter facts
  aren't touched here — re-run register-api to change `base_url` / `key_env`.
- `note "…"` — force a line into `log.md`.
- `reflect` — fold `log.md` into the `## Quirks` section of `{{NAME}}.md`, then archive
  (`reflect.sh archive-entity {{DIR}}`).
- `help` — this menu.

Endpoints / rate limits / billing / gotchas live in `{{NAME}}.md`; reflect maintains them. Lean.
